// reso-2.0-canonical.dbml
// Pure RESO Data Dictionary 2.0 canonical schema (2NF normalized)
// 41 Resources, 1530 Fields kept (1745 total - 215 satellites dropped), 193 Lookups
//
// NO Atlas-specific decisions baked in. This file represents what
// RESO 2.0 prescribes; Atlas adapts in build_atlas_target_dbml.py.
//
// Generated by reso-dd-kb/scripts/build_reso_canonical_dbml.py
// Source: dd.reso.org/DD2.0 + raw/fields.csv + raw/lookups.csv + raw/field_metadata.csv

Project reso_canonical_dd_2_0 {
  database_type: 'PostgreSQL'
  Note: '''
    Pure RESO Data Dictionary 2.0 canonical schema covering all 41 Resources,
    1530 Fields (1745 total minus 215 satellite fields dropped for 2NF),
    and 193 Lookups (rendered as lookup_<name> ref tables).

    2NF normalization: satellite fields (scalar columns whose name shares the
    prefix of a Resource-typed FK on the same host, e.g. Property.ListAgentEmail
    next to Property.ListAgent -> Member) are removed from the canonical model
    because their value is functionally dependent on the FK column rather than
    the host PK. They remain reachable via the FK join (or, in the case of
    auxiliary IDs / relationship attributes, would belong in a junction table).
    See the `// 2NF: dropped satellite fields` section below for the full list.

    Single-value lookup columns reference the corresponding lookup_<name>.code via DBML
    Refs; multi-value lookup columns stay text and document the lookup in a Note.

    No Atlas-specific decisions baked in. Atlas adapts this canonical in
    build_atlas_target_dbml.py (wiki/atlas/atlas-target.dbml), where a chosen
    subset of satellites may be re-added for query performance.
  '''
}

